{"lastModified":1774839699206,"uri":"c::10923570597::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Operating Area:\nBali, Lombok, Sumbawa, Sumba, Flores, Alor, Timor (Summer) & Ambon, Banda, Halmahera, Ternate, West Papua, Raja Ampat, Kaimana, Biak, Wakatobi (Winter)\n\nThe Ferretti 780 is 24 meters long and features a completely innovative internal yacht design and layout. The Ferretti 780 guarantees ample space and is finished in heartwood and teak rather than the traditional cherry wood which is used by most yacht manufacturers in yachts of this size. The flying bridge access stairs are integrated into the side of the yacht which means there is continual visibility from aft to bow. This design also increases the salon space in the superyacht which has two modern-styled sofas. Large windows allow a soothing feeling of proximity with the sea and nature and light furnishing lifts the spirit.\n\nThe Ferretti 780 master cabin with an extremely elegant environment and has a large en suite bathroom. The introduction of an aft garage means the 780 offers even more possibilities to take advantage of the external spaces, water toys, and swimming.","blueprint":{"name":"SAMKARA","images":["/media/media::image::c::10923570597::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1::assets::3db906f0-2be4-11f1-aa1d-e9b13f86e1a7/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::10923570597::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1::assets::3dba3f70-2be4-11f1-aa1d-e9b13f86e1a7/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::10923570597::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1::assets::3dc40370-2be4-11f1-aa1d-e9b13f86e1a7/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1::assets::800bbb10-bdfe-11ef-890b-7d8a24db4bf3/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd95f1::assets::800d41b0-bdfe-11ef-8cbe-0d7aa7f953b3/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::59b20f90-bdfa-11ef-9c9a-37d5f3cd